# Quality-First Shopify Theme Development

When designing or editing this Shopify theme, ALWAYS follow this workflow to minimize bugs.

---

## 1. Use Available Skills

Before and during design/code changes, apply these skills as relevant:

| Task | Skill to use |
|------|--------------|
| Any theme code change | **shopify-2026-standards** — mandatory for all edits |
| Sections, Liquid, Tailwind, GSAP, Web Components | **shopify-os2-architecture** |
| UI components, pages, visual design | **frontend-design** |
| Review UI, accessibility, best practices | **web-design-guidelines** |
| Animations, micro-interactions | **animate** |
| Before every push | **pre-push-audit** — 8 groups, no FAIL allowed |

---

## 2. Avoid "Fix One, Break Another"

When adding or modifying code:

- **Impact check**: Identify files/sections that reference or depend on what you're changing
- **Cross-reference**: After editing a section/snippet, grep for `render`, `section`, `include`, asset URLs that might be affected
- **Test related flows**: If you change cart-drawer, verify header badge, product add-to-cart, quick-view all still work
- **Schema changes**: If you change section schema (add/remove/rename settings), check `templates/*.json` and `config/settings_data.json` for orphan references

---

## 3. Pre-Push Audit (Mandatory)

Before `git push`, run **pre-push-audit** skill:

- [1] Liquid syntax
- [2] CSS conflicts
- [3] JS errors
- [4] Schema integrity
- [5] Broken references
- [6] Accessibility basics
- [7] Performance flags
- [8] Git hygiene

**Do NOT push if any FAIL.** Fix all FAILs first, then re-audit.

---

## 4. Regression Checklist

Before committing, verify:

- [ ] Changed sections still render correctly in theme editor
- [ ] No new console errors in DevTools
- [ ] Cart add/remove/update works (if cart-related changes)
- [ ] Responsive: test mobile viewport (≤375px)
- [ ] No merge conflict markers (`<<<<<<<`, `=======`, `>>>>>>>`) left in files

---

## 5. Order of Operations

```
1. Read relevant skills (shopify-2026-standards, shopify-os2-architecture, frontend-design)
2. Make edits with impact awareness
3. Run pre-push-audit
4. Fix any FAILs
5. Commit + push (per auto-push rule)
```

---

**Goal**: Minimize bugs. Use skills. Audit always. Avoid regressions.
